This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as word similarity and text classification. Additionally, the paper focuses on developing Chinese character embeddings, which is a specific area of NLP. 

The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to develop the models, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the exploration of semantic indicators in Chinese characters, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the retrieval of relevant information from text. 

Finally, the paper involves the development of bigram extensions to the models, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the use of neural networks for natural language processing tasks.
